olved, if at all.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Chair of PCP – perhaps </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Co-optee</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> due to independence</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">No personal point scoring by the PCC e.g. car insurance dodgers (The idea originated in Leicestershire in 2010)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Warwickshire PCC paying ambassadors £1,000 each to promote PCC?  (30 people I was told)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">One area paying Panel Members £10,000 p.a.?  If this is true it is not good.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">More PCP involvement in the selection of PCC staff – possibly during interviews.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Professional</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Barrier between PCC (his staff) and serving Police Officers</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">PCP 